------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Program : https://leetcode.com/problems/candy/description
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Companies : #amazon #apple #google #microsoft #salesforce #uber
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Problem : 

There are n children standing in a line. Each child is assigned a rating value given in the integer array ratings.

You are giving candies to these children subjected to the following requirements:

Each child must have at least one candy.
Children with a higher rating get more candies than their neighbors.
Return the minimum number of candies you need to have to distribute the candies to the children.

 

Example 1:

Input: ratings = [1,0,2]
Output: 5
Explanation: You can allocate to the first, second and third child with 2, 1, 2 candies respectively.
Example 2:

Input: ratings = [1,2,2]
Output: 4
Explanation: You can allocate to the first, second and third child with 1, 2, 1 candies respectively.
The third child gets 1 candy because it satisfies the above two conditions.
 

Constraints:

n == ratings.length
1 <= n <= 2 * 104
0 <= ratings[i] <= 2 * 104

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Explanation : 

we iterate the array.
when we iterate the array from left to right, if prev value is greater, we set current to prev+1.
when we iterate the array from right to left, if next curr is greater than previous (last), then we set current to last+1.
in both the above cases we set, the initial values to 1, because we have to give atleast 1 candy for a kid.

in the end we add max candies at each index.
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Solution :

class Solution {
    public int candy(int[] ratings) {
        int len = ratings.length;
        int[] pref = new int[len];
        pref[0]=1;
        int[] suff = new int[len];
        suff[len-1]=1;
        for(int i=1;i<len;i++){
            if(ratings[i]>ratings[i-1])
                pref[i]=pref[i-1]+1;
            else pref[i]=1;
        }
        for(int i=len-2;i>=0;i--){
            if(ratings[i+1]<ratings[i])
                suff[i]=suff[i+1]+1;
            else suff[i]=1;
        }
        int sum = 0;
        for(int i=0;i<len;i++){
            sum+=Math.max(pref[i],suff[i]);
        }
        return sum;
    }
}
